@page "/progress"
@rendermode InteractiveServer

<PageTitle>Project Progress</PageTitle>

<section class="hero">
    <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Project Progress</p>
        <h2>Track the prototype's delivery slice by slice.</h2>
        <p class="hero-copy">This page mirrors the repository progress tracker so the current state stays visible in the running app.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-stats">
        <div><span>1</span><label>Done</label></div>
        <div><span>2</span><label>In progress</label></div>
        <div><span>2</span><label>Next</label></div>
    </div>
</section>

<div class="grid-2">
    <article class="panel">
        <h3>Current snapshot</h3>
        <div class="list-row">
            <span>Solution foundation</span>
            <strong>Done</strong>
        </div>
        <div class="list-row">
            <span>Live football sync</span>
            <strong>In progress</strong>
        </div>
        <div class="list-row">
            <span>API and UI surface</span>
            <strong>In progress</strong>
        </div>
        <div class="list-row">
            <span>Historical data depth</span>
            <strong>Next</strong>
        </div>
        <div class="list-row">
            <span>Model maturity</span>
            <strong>Next</strong>
        </div>
    </article>

    <article class="panel">
        <h3>Near-term plan</h3>
        <ol class="progress-list">
            <li>Finish the historical import pipeline for fixtures and player match stats.</li>
            <li>Expand provider adapters behind the shared football data contract.</li>
            <li>Improve model features and training evaluation once the history layer is richer.</li>
            <li>Tighten operator workflows in the API and Web app as the data layer matures.</li>
        </ol>
    </article>
</div>

<article class="panel mt-4">
    <h3>How to update</h3>
    <p>When a discrete slice lands, update <code>docs/Progress.md</code>, add a delivery log row, and keep the snapshot aligned with the implementation state.</p>
</article>
